Package cs2030.simulator

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Server
    A server interface which provides the general method signature that all server types need to have.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Customer
    The Customer class encapsulates information and methods pertaining to a Customer in a simulation.
    HumanServer
    The Human Server class keeps track of who is the customer being served (if any) and who is the customer waiting to be served (if any).
    Pair<T,​U>
    This utility class stores two items together in a pair.
    PriorityQueue<T>
    This class wraps around the class PriorityQueue from Java Collection Framework.
    SelfCheckOutServer
    The SelfCheckOutServer class keeps track of who is the customer being served (if any) and who is the customer waiting to be served (if any) from the common queue.
    Shop
    A shop object maintains the list of servers and support queries for server.
    SimState
    This class encapsulates all the simulation states.
    Statistics
    This is an immutable class that stores stats about the simulation.
